<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-07T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-07T04:00:00-05:00" n="932" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d932">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/11–744: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-07T12:00:00+03:00">November
                                    7, 1944—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4260. ReDepts 2610, November 4, 8 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d932fn1">Not
                                printed; this telegram indicated that the Post Office Department
                                proposed to resume parcel post service immediately with all of the
                                Soviet Union (340.1115a/10–2844).</note> We have inquired through
                            the Foreign Office whether the Soviet postal authorities are agreeable
                            to the resumption of parcel post service from the U. S. to the Soviet
                            Union. We will endeavor to obtain an early reply but a delay of several
                            weeks is possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennan</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>